{
  "stem": "3206.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I-- when we were segregated, this was 1944, sometime in August, something like that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they were separating-- woman separate, men separate, kids, and things like that, young people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- and they send us from there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were-- there was one SS man.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I recall an incident when a mother-- a mother with a daughter-- the daughter was maybe 12, 14 years old-- and the mother didn't want to be separated from her daughter.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they were staying together, but they took the mother out someplace else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the daughter, they want to send someplace else.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the mother was starting-- she was holding on to her daughter-- and she was starting to scream, to cry no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The SS man went over, shot them both on the spot.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the segregation-- the mother would have-- I was down there, close, maybe one meter away, standing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was-- and then they separated us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One group, they sent I think to Buchenwald right away.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one group, which I was there, they send us to [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] called a place, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] near-- near Lodz.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You heard about Lodz, yeah?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Near there to dig trenches because the Russians were starting coming close.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they wanted to defend themselves, so trenches, you know like military trenches.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So how many were in your group that were sent?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the group was about 250 or something like that or more.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some of them people, which we lived through all those ordeals, they're still here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I still meet them all the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There, we were living in-- not in barracks, they didn't have no types of barracks, but they took away those barracks-- not barracks, but the barns from the farmers.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
